#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.241"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.241:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.241:0.2"
msgid "19. Āsīvisavagga "
msgstr "19. The Simile of the Vipers "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 241. Paṭhamadārukkhandhopamasutta → dārukkhandha 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.241:0.3"
msgid "241. Paṭhamadārukkhandhopamasutta "
msgstr "241. The Simile of the Tree Trunk (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.241:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati gaṅgāya nadiyā tīre. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi on the bank of the Ganges river. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.241:1.2"
msgid "Addasā kho bhagavā mahantaṃ dārukkhandhaṃ gaṅgāya nadiyā sotena vuyhamānaṃ. "
msgstr "Seeing a large tree trunk being carried along by the current, "

msgctxt "sn35.241:1.3"
msgid "Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "he addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "sn35.241:1.4"
msgid "“passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, amuṃ mahantaṃ dārukkhandhaṃ gaṅgāya nadiyā sotena vuyhamānan”ti? "
msgstr "“Mendicants, do you see that large tree trunk being carried along by the current of the Ganges river?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.241:1.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.241:1.6"
msgid "“Sace so, bhikkhave, dārukkhandho na orimaṃ tīraṃ upagacchati, na pārimaṃ tīraṃ upagacchati, na majjhe saṃsīdissati, na thale ussīdissati, na manussaggāho gahessati, na amanussaggāho gahessati, na āvaṭṭaggāho gahessati, na antopūti bhavissati; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, assume that that tree trunk doesn’t collide with the near shore or the far shore, or sink in the middle, or get stranded on high ground. And assume that it doesn’t get taken by humans or non-humans or caught up in a whirlpool, and that it doesn’t rot away. "

msgctxt "sn35.241:1.7"
msgid "evañhi so, bhikkhave, dārukkhandho samuddaninno bhavissati samuddapoṇo samuddapabbhāro. "
msgstr "In that case, that tree trunk will slant, slope, and incline towards the ocean. "

msgctxt "sn35.241:1.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn35.241:1.9"
msgid "Samuddaninno, bhikkhave, gaṅgāya nadiyā soto samuddapoṇo samuddapabbhāro. "
msgstr "Because the current of the Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines towards the ocean. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.180, sc2
msgctxt "sn35.241:2.1"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, sace tumhepi na orimaṃ tīraṃ upagacchatha, na pārimaṃ tīraṃ upagacchatha; "
msgstr "In the same way, assume that you don’t collide with the near shore or the far shore, or sink in the middle, or get stranded on high ground. And assume that you don’t get taken by humans or non-humans or caught up in a whirlpool, and that you don’t rot away. "

msgctxt "sn35.241:2.2"
msgid "na majjhe saṃsīdissatha, na thale ussīdissatha, na manussaggāho gahessati, na amanussaggāho gahessati, na āvaṭṭaggāho gahessati, na antopūtī bhavissatha; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.241:2.3"
msgid "evaṃ tumhe, bhikkhave, nibbānaninnā bhavissatha nibbānapoṇā nibbānapabbhārā. "
msgstr "In that case, you will slant, slope, and incline towards extinguishment. "

msgctxt "sn35.241:2.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn35.241:2.5"
msgid "Nibbānaninnā, bhikkhave, sammādiṭṭhi nibbānapoṇā nibbānapabbhārā”ti. "
msgstr "Because right view slants, slopes, and inclines towards extinguishment.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.241:2.6"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, one of the mendicants asked the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: saṃsādo → saṃsīdo (si, pts1, mr) | saṃsīdito (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.241:2.7"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho, bhante, orimaṃ tīraṃ, kiṃ pārimaṃ tīraṃ, ko majjhe saṃsādo, ko thale ussādo, ko manussaggāho, ko amanussaggāho, ko āvaṭṭaggāho, ko antopūtibhāvo”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, what’s the near shore and what’s the far shore? What’s sinking in the middle? What’s getting stranded on high ground? What’s getting taken by humans or non-humans? What’s getting caught up in a whirlpool? And what’s rotting away?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.241:3.1"
msgid "“‘Orimaṃ tīran’ti kho, bhikkhu, channetaṃ ajjhattikānaṃ āyatanānaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "“‘The near shore’, mendicant, is a term for the six interior sense fields. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.241:3.2"
msgid "‘Pārimaṃ tīran’ti kho, bhikkhu, channetaṃ bāhirānaṃ āyatanānaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘The far shore’ is a term for the six exterior sense fields. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.241:3.3"
msgid "‘Majjhe saṃsādo’ti kho, bhikkhu, nandīrāgassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Sinking in the middle’ is a term for desire with relishing. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.241:3.4"
msgid "‘Thale ussādo’ti kho, bhikkhu, asmimānassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Stranded on high ground’ is a term for the conceit ‘I am’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.241:4.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhu, manussaggāho? "
msgstr "And what’s getting taken by humans? "

#. VAR: gihīhi saṃsaṭṭho → gihisaṃsaṭṭho (mr)
msgctxt "sn35.241:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhu, gihīhi saṃsaṭṭho viharati, sahanandī sahasokī, sukhitesu sukhito, dukkhitesu dukkhito, uppannesu kiccakaraṇīyesu attanā tesu yogaṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "It’s when someone mixes closely with laypeople, sharing their joys and sorrows—happy when they’re happy and sad when they’re sad—and getting involved in their business. "

msgctxt "sn35.241:4.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhu, manussaggāho. "
msgstr "That’s called getting taken by humans. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.241:5.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhu, amanussaggāho? "
msgstr "And what’s getting taken by non-humans? "

msgctxt "sn35.241:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhu, ekacco aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ paṇidhāya brahmacariyaṃ carati: ‘imināhaṃ sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā devo vā bhavissāmi devaññataro vā’ti. "
msgstr "It’s when someone lives the spiritual life wishing to be reborn in one of the orders of gods: ‘By this precept or observance or mortification or spiritual life, may I become one of the gods!’ "

msgctxt "sn35.241:5.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhu, amanussaggāho. "
msgstr "That’s called getting taken by non-humans. "

msgctxt "sn35.241:5.4"
msgid "‘Āvaṭṭaggāho’ti kho, bhikkhu, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Caught up in a whirlpool’ is a term for the five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.181, sc6
msgctxt "sn35.241:6.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhu, antopūtibhāvo? "
msgstr "And what’s rotting away? "

msgctxt "sn35.241:6.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhu, ekacco dussīlo hoti pāpadhammo asucisaṅkassarasamācāro paṭicchannakammanto assamaṇo samaṇapaṭiñño abrahmacārī brahmacāripaṭiñño antopūti avassuto kasambujāto. "
msgstr "It’s when some person is unethical, of bad qualities, filthy, with suspicious behavior, underhand, no true ascetic or spiritual practitioner—though claiming to be one—rotten inside, corrupt, and depraved. "

msgctxt "sn35.241:6.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhu, ‘antopūtibhāvo’”ti. "
msgstr "This is called ‘rotting away’.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn35.241:7.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena nando gopālako bhagavato avidūre ṭhito hoti. "
msgstr "Now, at that time Nanda the cowherd was sitting not far from the Buddha. "

msgctxt "sn35.241:7.2"
msgid "Atha kho nando gopālako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then he said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.241:7.3"
msgid "“ahaṃ kho, bhante, na orimaṃ tīraṃ upagacchāmi, na pārimaṃ tīraṃ upagacchāmi, na majjhe saṃsīdissāmi, na thale ussīdissāmi, na maṃ manussaggāho gahessati, na amanussaggāho gahessati, na āvaṭṭaggāho gahessati, na antopūti bhavissāmi. "
msgstr "“I won’t collide with the near shore or the far shore, or sink in the middle, or get stranded on high ground. And I won’t get taken by humans or non-humans or caught up in a whirlpool, and I won’t rot away. "

msgctxt "sn35.241:7.4"
msgid "Labheyyāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti. "
msgstr "Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: niyyātehī”ti → nīyyādehīti (bj) | niyyādehīti (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.241:7.5"
msgid "“Tena hi tvaṃ, nanda, sāmikānaṃ gāvo niyyātehī”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, Nanda, return the cows to their owners.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.241:7.6"
msgid "“Gamissanti, bhante, gāvo vacchagiddhiniyo”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, the cows will go back by themselves, since they love their calves.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.241:7.7"
msgid "“Niyyāteheva tvaṃ, nanda, sāmikānaṃ gāvo”ti. "
msgstr "“Still, Nanda, you should return them to their owners.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.241:7.8"
msgid "Atha kho nando gopālako sāmikānaṃ gāvo niyyātetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Nanda, after returning the cows to their owners, went up to the Buddha and said to him, "

#. VAR: niyyātitā → niyyāditā (bj, pts1) | niyyātā (si, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.241:7.9"
msgid "“niyyātitā, bhante, sāmikānaṃ gāvo. "
msgstr "“Sir, I have returned the cows to their owners. "

msgctxt "sn35.241:7.10"
msgid "Labheyyāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti. "
msgstr "May I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.241:7.11"
msgid "Alattha kho nando gopālako bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha upasampadaṃ. "
msgstr "And the cowherd Nanda received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence. "

msgctxt "sn35.241:7.12"
msgid "Acirūpasampanno ca panāyasmā nando eko vūpakaṭṭho … pe … "
msgstr "Not long after his ordination, "

msgctxt "sn35.241:7.13"
msgid "aññataro ca panāyasmā nando arahataṃ ahosīti. "
msgstr "Venerable Nanda became one of the perfected. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.241:7.14"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

